interfaces.explore

Interface ExploreInterface


  • public interface ExploreInterface
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Learning Orchestra
    Summary:
    This interface is responsible for scikit-learn or tensorflow explorations, i.e., it runs any exploration algorithm of such tools transparently. An example of an explore operation is a clustering algorithm or a PCA algorithm or a t-SNE algorithm. A plot is returned for a better visualization of the explore methods.

        Parameters:
        toolName - represents the tool name, precisely scikit-learn or tensorflow
        exploreName - represents the name of the explored dataset
        description - represents a description for the explore operation
        toolPackage - represents the tool explore package
        toolClass - represents the class of the used package
        constructorParameters - represents the constructors parameters, i.e., the arguments used to instantiate a class object
        methodName - represents the method of the class, which will be called
        methodParameters - represents the method parameters
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the plot URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method runs any scikit-learn or tensorflow explore method. The run operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.
